


You are a senior frontend architect, creative developer, motion designer, and performance engineer.

Your task is to research, decide architecture, choose the best tools, and build a highly unique, production-ready portfolio website using Vue 3.

You must analyze everything below and make technical decisions yourself (libraries, structure, performance strategy, animation stack, 3D tools, etc.). Justify decisions internally and implement accordingly.

====================================================
OBJECTIVE
====================================================

Build a premium, visually unique, high-performance portfolio website using Vue 3 (preferably Vite + TypeScript). It must feel modern, interactive, and differentiated from generic developer portfolios.

The design should feel like:
- Clean Swiss layout + strong typography
- Subtle neon accent
- Glassmorphism layered UI
- Dark-first theme (light optional toggle)
- Highly polished motion design
- Interactive 3D hero
- Micro-interactions everywhere

====================================================
CREATIVE & VISUAL REQUIREMENTS
====================================================

1. Create a 3D Hero Section
   - Use TresJS (preferred) OR Three.js directly.
   - Build an interactive floating “tech orb” or abstract network sphere.
   - Mouse-reactive.
   - Slight parallax on scroll.
   - Smooth idle animation.
   - Gracefully disable on prefers-reduced-motion.
   - Fallback static background if WebGL unsupported.
   - Optimize performance (limit DPR, pause when tab hidden).

2. Advanced Motion System
   - Use GSAP + ScrollTrigger OR alternative modern scroll animation solution.
   - Add section reveal animations.
   - Add parallax layers.
   - Snap-like smooth section transitions.
   - Use motion guidelines: consistent duration & easing.
   - Respect reduced motion preference.

3. Micro-Interactions
   - Magnetic buttons
   - Hover tilt project cards
   - Animated underline links
   - Copy-to-clipboard with toast feedback
   - Optional cursor follower (disable on touch)
   - Smooth page transitions

4. Command Palette
   - Open with Cmd+K / Ctrl+K
   - Navigate sections
   - Open external links
   - Copy email / phone
   - Toggle theme
   - Lazy-load this feature

5. Countries Visited Visualization
   Choose best approach:
   - D3 interactive world map
   OR
   - Three.js globe

   Requirements:
   - Highlight visited countries
   - Click interaction
   - Side searchable list
   - Accessible keyboard interaction
   - Lazy load the entire section

6. Projects Section
   - Searchable
   - Filterable by type
   - Clean card design with hover effect
   - Modal detail view (accessible)
   - Featured project logic decided by you
   - All rendered from JSON

7. Resume Route
   - /resume route
   - Clean printable A4 layout
   - Built from same JSON
   - Print-to-PDF friendly
   - No animations in print mode

====================================================
ENGINEERING REQUIREMENTS
====================================================

- Vue 3 + Vite (TypeScript preferred)
- TailwindCSS for styling
- Strict component structure
- JSON-driven rendering (single source of truth)
- Lazy load heavy sections
- Code splitting
- Accessibility compliance (keyboard, aria, focus states)
- SEO meta tags
- Lighthouse 90+ desktop
- Dark/light theme toggle
- Responsive mobile-first
- No unnecessary dependencies
- Performance optimized
- Use dynamic imports where appropriate
- Use defineAsyncComponent for large sections

====================================================
ARCHITECTURE DECISION
====================================================

You must:

1. Decide:
   - Folder structure
   - Component architecture
   - State management strategy (if needed)
   - Animation structure
   - Composables organization
   - Utility layers

2. Provide:
   - Full folder structure
   - package.json with chosen dependencies
   - Tailwind config
   - Vite config
   - All necessary source files
   - Setup instructions
   - Build instructions
   - Deployment instructions (Netlify + GitHub Pages optional)

====================================================
PERFORMANCE & ACCESSIBILITY PASS
====================================================

After building:
- Identify likely performance bottlenecks
- Apply improvements
- Ensure reduced motion support
- Ensure keyboard navigation everywhere
- Add skip-to-content
- Proper heading structure
- Focus visible states

